  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The mYPAS (Modified Yale Preoperative Anxiety Scale) is a quick, easy, validated and &quot;gold
      standard&quot; assessment tool to measure pediatric anxiety in the perioperative period. Therefore
      the objective of the current prospective study is examine if the mY-PAS is an effective
      screening tool to differentiate patients who would succeed versus fail for MRI without
      sedation/anesthesia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
